âˆ™âˆ™\bullet Vertical regime. We strive to present DVPL-Katyusha and DVPL-Katyusha with scalar compression (Algorithm 2 and 3 respectively) â€” algorithms with compression working under the assumption of the vertical data division. The first one uses RandK compressor, and the second utilize MSE loss and arbitrary (with respect to Definition 1.1) compressor. In both algorithms every worker sends its own part of scalar values, needed to calculate total loss, and then perform other part of L-Katyusha locally with its own set of features. We estimate the asymptotics in such settings and show a lower bound for scalar compression on a constructive example. We are one of the first to present algorithm with vertical regime and guaranties for theoretical convergence.
